-- American Water Pennsylvania Unit Closes Year With Two Purchases
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-01-02T16:18:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-02/american-water-pennsylvania-unit-closes-year-with-two-purchases.html
American Water Works Co. (AWK)  closed the
year with two acquisitions by its  Pennsylvania  subsidiary, the
biggest publicly traded water company in the U.S. said.  The $1.2 million of purchases in northeast Pennsylvania
were for water assets that serve the Fernwood Resort in Monroe
County and the All Seasons Water Co. in Pike County, the
Voorhees, N.J.-based utility said in a statement. American Water
shares have risen 22 percent over the past year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
